## Agent Pipeline
```
requirements-agent в†’ ui-design-agent в†’ planner-agent в†’ test-definer-agent в†’ ticket-writer-agent
                                                                                      в†“
                                                                         [review tickets in git]
                                                                                      в†“
                                                          unit-test-writer + e2e-test-writer  в†ђ failing specs first
                                                                                      в†“
                                                    db в†’ storage в†’ api в†’ auth в†’ ui   в†ђ each atomic commit
                                                                                      в†“
                                                              e2e-runner в†’ mutation-tester в†’ reviewer
```

---

## Setting Up in a New Project

### 1. Add as a submodule
```bash
git submodule add git@github.com:you/agent-stack.git .cursor/shared
git submodule update --init
```

### 2. Symlink into Cursor's expected paths
```bash
# Core вЂ” always loaded in every project
ln -s .cursor/shared/core/agents   .cursor/agents/core
ln -s .cursor/shared/core/skills   .cursor/skills/core

# Stack вЂ” pick your stack
ln -s .cursor/shared/stacks/react-hono-trpc/agents  .cursor/agents/stack
ln -s .cursor/shared/stacks/react-hono-trpc/skills  .cursor/skills/stack

# Shared tooling
ln -s .cursor/shared/hooks     .cursor/hooks
ln -s .cursor/shared/commands  .cursor/commands
```

For an Electron project, add the override layer on top:
```bash
ln -s .cursor/shared/stacks/electron/agents  .cursor/agents/electron
ln -s .cursor/shared/stacks/electron/skills  .cursor/skills/electron
```

### 3. Create your project AGENT.md
```bash
touch .cursor/AGENT.md
```

Minimal content:
```markdown
## Stack
react-hono-trpc

## Layers loaded
- .cursor/agents/core
- .cursor/agents/stack

## Project-specific notes
- DB: Supabase (self-hosted)
- Auth: Better Auth with session strategy
- No overrides вЂ” all shared agents apply as-is
```

### 4. Configure MCP servers

Create `.cursor/mcp.json` in your project:
```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "supabase": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": [
        "-y",
        "@supabase/mcp-server-supabase@latest",
        "--supabase-url", "https://your-project.supabase.co",
        "--supabase-key", "${SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY}",
        "--features", "database,storage"
      ]
    },
    "playwright": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["@playwright/mcp@latest"]
    }
  }
}
```

---

## Keeping Projects Up to Date

When you improve an agent or skill in this repo:
```bash
# In agent-stack
git commit -m "refactor: improve ticket-writer prompt"
git push

# In any project using it
git submodule update --remote --merge
```

Add this alias to your shell to make it a one-liner:
```bash
# .zshrc or .bashrc
alias ai-sync="git submodule update --remote --merge"
```

Then syncing any project is just:
```bash
ai-sync
```

---

## Override Priority

When Cursor loads agents and skills, project-level files always win:
```
1. .cursor/agents/          в†ђ project-specific, highest priority
2. .cursor/agents/electron  в†ђ electron stack override (if loaded)
3. .cursor/agents/stack     в†ђ base stack (react-hono-trpc)
4. .cursor/agents/core      в†ђ tech-agnostic baseline
```

---

## Versioning

Tag stable states of the repo so projects can pin to a known-good version:
```bash
git tag -a v1.0.0 -m "stable: react-hono-trpc stack complete"
git push --tags
```

Pin a project to a specific version:
```bash
cd your-project
git -C .cursor/shared checkout v1.0.0
```
